      <h4 class="bold">What are fine particles?</h4>
      <p>
        Fine Particulate Matter or PM<sub>2.5</sub> refers to particles of matter suspended in the air that are 2.5 micrometers in diameter or smaller.
        That's 30 times smaller than the diameter of a single human hair!
      </p>
