      <h4 class="bold">What are the health effects of fine particles?</h4>
      <p>
        Fine particles have been identified by the Environmental Protection Agency
        and the American Lung Association as an air pollutant that can be very harmful
        to your health. Inhaling PM<sub>2.5</sub> can cause coughing or wheezing.
        Exposure over extended periods of time can contribute to or worsen illnesses
        such as asthma, heart disease, chronic bronchitis, emphysema and pneumonia.
      </p>
